						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="bold">Śaka 1577 (1655 A.D.)</hi></p>						

						<p>Damaged and faintly engraved. Seems to record a gift of money by Vasantarāyaṉ for conducting the sixth day festival of the Kṛishṇayyatirunāḷ of the god when the deity would be seated in the pavilion at Muttaraśanallūr. Gives a long list of the various provisions made for the occasion. The details of the date viz., <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1577, Manmatha, Dhanus, śu. 3, Thursday</hi> regularly correspond <hi rend="bold">to 1655, A.D. December 20, Thursday, ·91; ·62.</hi></p>						

						<p>1. The following short inscription is engraved on a pillar in the maṇḍapa.</p>						

						</summary>
